               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370703-name-519" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370703-name-519" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370703-name-519" type="surname" value="GASELEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370703-name-519" type="given" value="GEORGE ALEXANDER"></interp>GEORGE ALEXANDER GASELEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a French polisher, and live at No. 17, Berwick-street, St. James's. The prisoner lodged in a room with me—I left him in bed on the 9th of January, and left the two coats and other things in the room—when I came back, they and the prisoner were gone.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183707030072"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370703-name-520" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370703-name-520" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370703-name-520" type="surname" value="BRILLARD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370703-name-520" type="given" value="SUSANNAH"></interp>SUSANNAH BRILLARD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of an eating-house keeper in Berwick-street. The prisoner lodges with me—I remember his coming down that morning—he brought two coats, a waistcoat, and two pairs of trowsers down with him—he told me he was going to leave them at the workshop of Gaseley—he did not come back.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Did you see these things? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, in your hands, but not the shirts—you said you should be back in an hour and settle with me, and did not come back any more.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370703-name-521" type="witnessName">
